WEBVTT

00:04:58.556 --> 00:05:01.017
The problem is that unless we do
something about it,

00:05:01.041 --> 00:05:03.430
that is the way the world will always be.

00:05:04.628 --> 00:05:06.460
So why should you care about this?

00:05:06.484 --> 00:05:07.639
Right?

00:05:07.663 --> 00:05:10.898
I mean, we're facing some rather
significant problems in the world

00:05:10.922 --> 00:05:12.074
just at present,

00:05:12.098 --> 00:05:14.437
what does it really matter
if I can't get a job,

00:05:14.461 --> 00:05:16.784
or you're stuck watching
"Transformer 17," right?

00:05:16.808 --> 00:05:18.546
(Laughter)

00:05:18.570 --> 00:05:20.887
Well, let me put it to you this way:

00:05:20.911 --> 00:05:22.295
the year "Jaws" came out,

00:05:22.319 --> 00:05:27.042
Americans suddenly started listing
"sharks" among their top 10 major fears.

00:05:28.010 --> 00:05:33.696
In 1995, BMW paid the James Bond franchise
three million dollars